Responsibilities

What You’ll Do

The primary responsibilities for this position include but are not limited to:

Build and optimize Android applications and services for in-vehicle infotainment platforms.
Develop voice-driven features that integrate speech, audio, conversational AI, and agentic workflows.
Work with Android audio pipelines, media, microphone input, routing, focus, and low-latency audio behavior.
Integrate and optimize embedded AI/SLM capabilities for on-device or hybrid vehicle experiences.
Design and implement modern, maintainable app architectures using current Android development best practices.
Partner with product, UX, platform, systems, and AI teams to deliver intuitive voice experiences in production vehicles.
Debug complex issues across app, framework, audio, connectivity, and embedded environments.
Help define technical direction, engineering standards, and scalable patterns for future capabilities.


Qualifications

You'll have... 

Education: Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related technical field.(Successful candidates will be required to provide proof of completion for the highest level of education attained. If the diploma/degree was obtained from a school outside of Canada, an Education Credential Assessment report showing Canadian equivalency is also required).

Experience:

5+ years' experience in Android development experience with Kotlin and modern Android frameworks.
2+ years' experience understanding of the Android audio subsystem, including audio focus, capture, routing, media/session behavior, and troubleshooting.
Proven experience with modern application development practices: clean architecture, modularization, testing, observability, CI/CD, and performance optimization.
Understanding of embedded AI, on-device inference, Small Language Models, or edge Machine Learning deployments.


Even better, you may have...

Proven communication skills and comfort working in cross-functional product and platform teams.
Ability to work across software layers and debug issues in complex integrated systems.
Experience building voice applications, conversational interfaces, or speech-enabled products.
Experience with Android Automotive OS, embedded Android, or infotainment systems.
Background in wake word, ASR, TTS, dialog systems, or multimodal assistant experiences.
Experience optimizing models or inference pipelines for constrained hardware environments.
Familiarity with automotive, real-time, or safety-conscious product development.
 Experience shipping consumer-facing products at scale. 


